1
00:00:01,920 --> 00:00:07,010
Here's my setup, based on Nikola Tesla's early ideas,

2
00:00:11,220 --> 00:00:14,880
which disproves Ohm's law for a circuit segment.

3
00:00:18,630 --> 00:00:20,880
Now we'll see how it works.

4
00:00:22,560 --> 00:00:24,740
Powering it up.

5
00:00:39,740 --> 00:00:41,500
The lamp lights up.

6
00:00:43,180 --> 00:00:47,380
It serves as a voltage indicator on this big conductor.

7
00:00:49,600 --> 00:00:52,140
I'll add that this is one and the same conductor.

8
00:00:52,700 --> 00:00:57,500
The lamp is attached to it — and that's all there is here.

9
00:00:58,500 --> 00:01:04,560
The lamp's glow depends on the discharge frequency.

10
00:01:06,540 --> 00:01:10,840
We're changing it slightly now, and the glow varies.

11
00:01:13,320 --> 00:01:16,340
This is the big conductor.

12
00:01:17,920 --> 00:01:19,800
And the lamp hangs on it.

13
00:01:25,080 --> 00:01:29,020
You can even hang it on one

14
00:01:30,020 --> 00:01:34,020
of the shorter wire segments.

15
00:01:36,850 --> 00:01:40,830
And the filament will still glow.

16
00:01:41,790 --> 00:01:43,650
Just not as intensely.

17
00:01:50,170 --> 00:01:51,270
I'll add

18
00:02:04,060 --> 00:02:07,240
once more — this is one and the same conductor.

19
00:02:15,350 --> 00:02:16,910
There's a discharge.

20
00:02:16,910 --> 00:02:18,030
And

21
00:02:21,510 --> 00:02:23,930
the lamp glows — the lamp.

22
00:02:24,110 --> 00:02:26,830
Standard automotive, 12-volt.
